J‘J‘ Back-door screen is slamming J‘J‘

31:06.198 --> 31:07.324
[Vic]
Hmm.

31:08.034 --> 31:09.399
So, I take it
round two with Walt

31:09.618 --> 31:11.404
didn't go as well as expected?

31:14.915 --> 31:17.372
You know, I really don't need
any shit right now.

31:18.502 --> 31:20.367
No shit. Just beer.

31:22.923 --> 31:25.585
Did you really think
he was gonna hire you, though?

31:27.887 --> 31:29.878
I thought he'd give me a chance.

31:31.057 --> 31:34.515
-You have a record, Travis.
-Misdemeanors.

31:34.727 --> 31:38.185
Dumb mistakes. Or maybe you
don't have any of those.

31:38.397 --> 31:41.434
You know, I may not come
from money like Branch did.

31:41.650 --> 31:43.356
But I'll tell you one thing --
I'm a much better person

31:45.863 --> 31:47.774
But would you have made
a better deputy?

31:50.743 --> 31:52.859
You know, me and Branch,

31:53.079 --> 31:55.161
we played football ever since
we were little kids,

31:55.373 --> 31:56.704
and he was always
the starting QB.

31:56.916 --> 31:58.998
And me,
I was just a blocking back.

31:59.210 --> 32:01.667
But when we graduated
from high school,

32:01.879 --> 32:04.120
guess who went on
to play Division I football.

32:05.174 --> 32:06.960
It sure as hell
wasn't Branch Connally.

32:07.176 --> 32:08.632
And why's that?

32:08.844 --> 32:10.550
Because I played harder
than he did

32:10.805 --> 32:12.636
and because I cared more
about helping my team

32:12.848 --> 32:14.258
than padding my own stats.

32:14.475 --> 32:16.761
You know, that's --
that's the thing

32:16.936 --> 32:19.143
that pisses me off
about this the most.

32:19.355 --> 32:21.721
It's that I can accept going out
there on the field and losing.

32:21.941 --> 32:25.104
What I can't accept is not even
being given a goddamn chance.

32:28.823 --> 32:32.065
J‘J‘ Don't let the sweet
still love me J‘J‘

32:32.910 --> 32:36.277
J‘J‘ Just got to try again J‘J‘

32:37.289 --> 32:40.622
If Next time, nothing
will stop me J‘J‘

32:41.502 --> 32:43.333
N You know you want it J‘J‘

32:56.225 --> 32:58.341
[Vic] Any word
on Brandi Collette's ring?

32:59.186 --> 33:00.847
Not yet.

33:01.063 --> 33:03.770
God help me if I find whoever
stole it.

33:04.650 --> 33:08.814
So, I've been thinking about
this warehouse robbery.

33:09.613 --> 33:12.195
Maybe the pseudoephedrine
wasn't actually the target.

33:12.408 --> 33:14.740
You think they were after
the Zoloft?

33:14.952 --> 33:17.159
Yeah, well,
I Googled it last night.

33:17.371 --> 33:20.534
Zoloft is prescribed a lot
for people with PTSD.

33:20.749 --> 33:22.580
If somebody knew about
Brandi's Collette's condition,

33:22.793 --> 33:24.169
they might have assumed
that she was on Zoloft

33:24.378 --> 33:25.959
while she was alive.

33:26.172 --> 33:29.414
And a cabinet full of pills
after she wasn't, so...

33:29.633 --> 33:30.668
Right.

33:32.887 --> 33:35.754
Yo, Sheriff, your narc sucks.

33:36.599 --> 33:38.840
You guys stop by to pick up
your pseudo?

33:39.059 --> 33:42.222
You guys couldn't break us,
so you sent your undercover pig

33:42.438 --> 33:45.100
to try and peddle off
some baggies of Z-loft on us

33:45.316 --> 33:46.431
at like half-price.

33:46.650 --> 33:48.265
I didn't send anybody
to do that.

33:48.486 --> 33:51.569
Well, Dwight Brisco sure as shit
looked and acted like a cop.

33:51.780 --> 33:53.111
We've already sent this
asshole's photo

33:53.324 --> 33:54.484
to everyone that we know.

33:54.700 --> 33:56.236
So Mr. 22 Jump Street's act

33:56.452 --> 33:57.942
is totally defunct.

33:58.162 --> 33:59.151
[Walt]
Oh, I see.

33:59.371 --> 34:00.907
Ah!

34:01.123 --> 34:03.785
Dude, that's his new phone.

34:04.001 --> 34:05.286
Which I can search,

34:05.503 --> 34:07.209
according to the terms
of your probation.

34:07.421 --> 34:10.458
If you've got any questions
about the legality of all this,

34:10.674 --> 34:12.505
we can call
your probation officer right now

34:12.718 --> 34:14.549
and go over the details.

34:23.062 --> 34:24.802
It's nice weather, huh?

34:28.317 --> 34:32.560
Once you slide that bag my way,
I will take it and walk away.

34:32.780 --> 34:35.317
You will find an envelope
full of money under the bench,

34:35.533 --> 34:36.943
as discussed.

34:58.389 --> 35:00.095
Shit.

35:00.307 --> 35:01.592
You seem to be in a hurry

35:01.809 --> 35:03.925
to sell off those pills
for cheap.

35:05.604 --> 35:07.344
Most street dealers I know

35:07.565 --> 35:09.556
make their money just selling
a little bit at a time.

35:09.775 --> 35:11.891
I'm not a dealer.
I'm an idiot.

35:18.075 --> 35:21.067
And a broke vet
with too many bills.

35:21.287 --> 35:23.778
Think that makes it okay
to peddle illegal drugs?

35:23.998 --> 35:25.829
l was desperate, okay?

35:26.041 --> 35:27.451
Every single job I apply for,

35:27.668 --> 35:29.283
every single job, you know
what they tell me?

35:29.503 --> 35:31.118
They say I don't have
the right education

35:31.338 --> 35:32.669
or the right experience.

35:32.881 --> 35:34.257
Apparently my military service,

35:34.466 --> 35:36.331
well, that's just a black mark
on my résumé.

35:36.552 --> 35:38.258
They all think that I've got
PTSD, TBI,

35:38.470 --> 35:40.426
or some other alphabet soup
that's gonna have me

35:40.639 --> 35:42.140
shooting up the place
or something.

35:42.891 --> 35:46.509
So, your solution is to steal
some Zoloft pills and sell them?

35:46.729 --> 35:49.015
I didn't -- I didn't steal them.

35:49.231 --> 35:50.220
I found them.

35:50.816 --> 35:52.147
Yes, like Columbus
found America.

35:52.359 --> 35:54.020
No, seriously.

35:55.321 --> 35:57.027
I heard about this church
on Highway 12,

35:57.239 --> 35:58.854
and they had a stash
of free anti-depressants

35:59.074 --> 36:00.530
for vets in need.

36:00.743 --> 36:02.734
So I went to the church,
I dug around. I found some.

36:03.412 --> 36:05.323
Hey, everybody assumes

36:05.497 --> 36:07.408
that I'm this
traumatized vet anyway.

36:07.625 --> 36:09.832
I might as well profit from it.

36:10.044 --> 36:12.626
So, who's distributing
these pills for free?

36:13.839 --> 36:15.204
I don't know.

36:15.424 --> 36:17.164
I just kind of assumed
it was Hector.

36:17.384 --> 36:19.636
Hector is dead.

36:19.845 --> 36:21.801
No, he's not, man.

36:22.014 --> 36:25.177
You ask anybody on the Res.
Hector lives.

36:36.236 --> 36:38.693
You do surveillance
like this often?

36:40.741 --> 36:42.356
Whenever Walt tells me to.

36:43.285 --> 36:45.947
Yeah, and he sounds like a boss
that you don't want to cross.

36:46.163 --> 36:48.028
[Ferg]
What do you mean?

36:48.248 --> 36:50.580
Well, didn't he hunt down
and gut the guy

36:50.793 --> 36:53.205
that murdered his wife
Charles Bronson-style?

36:53.420 --> 36:56.207
He was under federal
investigation for it, right?

36:56.423 --> 36:58.539
And cleared of any wrongdoing.

36:58.759 --> 36:59.748
Right.

37:00.761 --> 37:02.001
Hey, sorry, Ferg.

37:02.471 --> 37:04.302
I just want to know
what I'm getting myself into.

37:04.515 --> 37:06.676
You know what I mean?
My instructors at the academy,

37:06.892 --> 37:08.257
they were really by-the-book.

37:08.477 --> 37:09.512
Here, you can drive
whatever you want.

37:09.728 --> 37:10.843
You can wear whatever you want.

37:11.063 --> 37:12.553
Hell, it's like the sheriff

37:12.773 --> 37:15.685
cares more about books
than physical fitness.

37:15.901 --> 37:18.108
-You know what I mean?
-That's the third time.

37:18.320 --> 37:20.732
-Third time what?
-Third time that truck's driven

37:20.948 --> 37:22.484
past us.

37:22.700 --> 37:24.816
Is it a blue pickup with
Colorado plates, right?

37:25.035 --> 37:27.868
-Yep.
-Yeah, we've been made. [sighs]

37:28.080 --> 37:30.071
What, you think someone's trying
to get at Lee McKinnon?

37:30.290 --> 37:31.575
Well, if they are,
they're not gonna do it

37:31.792 --> 37:33.498
with me sitting here
in my uniform.

37:33.711 --> 37:35.451
Look, I'm gonna drive off,

37:35.671 --> 37:36.877
but I'm gonna leave
one of you here

37:37.089 --> 37:38.204
to see if that truck comes back.

37:38.424 --> 37:39.755
Yeah, I got it.

37:39.967 --> 37:42.800
Uh, don't take this
the wrong way, Monte,

37:43.011 --> 37:46.174
but you look exactly like a cop.

37:46.390 --> 37:47.596
[chuckles]

37:47.808 --> 37:48.923
Zachary's got this one.

37:49.143 --> 37:50.508
[Zachary]
All right.

37:50.728 --> 37:52.514
-Got to let him out.
-Sorry.

37:52.730 --> 37:53.890
Push it up.

37:56.608 --> 37:57.814
[Ferg]
Zachary.

37:59.361 --> 38:00.862
Take this.

38:01.071 --> 38:02.936
Pretend you're getting
signatures for a petition.

38:03.157 --> 38:04.021
All right.

38:04.241 --> 38:06.197
[engine turns over]

38:16.670 --> 38:18.126
[Vic] So, this Dwight Brisco guy

38:18.338 --> 38:20.124
said he got the anti-depressants
from inside here?

38:20.340 --> 38:21.955
He also said
Hector's still alive,

38:22.176 --> 38:24.758
so I'm not sure
how reliable he is.

38:27.431 --> 38:30.138
So, you're taking this search
pretty seriously.

38:31.226 --> 38:33.478
Of course
I'm taking it seriously.

38:33.687 --> 38:35.894
Two people have been shot.

38:36.106 --> 38:38.973
I was talking about
the deputy search.

38:41.361 --> 38:45.445
Well,
can't get it wrong again...

38:46.366 --> 38:47.742
...and hire another deputy

38:47.951 --> 38:50.283
who can't handle the strain
of the job.

38:51.288 --> 38:53.654
I noticed you've been pretty
quiet about the whole thing.

38:54.541 --> 38:56.077
What do you think
of the candidates?

38:57.085 --> 38:59.292
I think I should
just leave that up to you.

39:00.422 --> 39:02.538
I haven't been the best judge
of character lately.

39:04.301 --> 39:05.802
[notes play]

39:09.598 --> 39:11.839
[piano key clicks]

39:12.059 --> 39:13.265
[Clicking]

39:32.120 --> 39:35.032
So, we're looking for
a patriotic Robin Hood?

39:35.249 --> 39:36.455
Yeah.

39:36.667 --> 39:39.283
[boy imitating airplane]

39:49.471 --> 39:51.507
Gather up all the pills
that you find.

40:06.196 --> 40:07.811
[indistinct talking]

40:24.631 --> 40:25.882
Bible study?

40:26.091 --> 40:28.628
Support group for Army wives.

40:28.844 --> 40:31.335
Quack from the V.A.
organized it.

40:32.639 --> 40:34.254
[Rebecca]
Gareth wasn't even eating.

40:34.474 --> 40:38.513
He believes that tapeworms
were living under his scars

40:38.729 --> 40:40.685
and feeding off of everything
that he ate.

40:40.898 --> 40:42.229
How is Gareth now?

40:43.066 --> 40:45.899
Uh... better.

40:46.111 --> 40:49.353
He came with me today,
and he's eating again.

40:49.573 --> 40:51.154
Good.

40:51.617 --> 40:54.233
I still -- I still
don't feel comfortable

40:54.453 --> 40:56.284
leaving him alone with Eli.

40:56.496 --> 40:57.656
That's okay.

40:57.873 --> 41:01.707
But... he's better.

41:03.420 --> 41:04.626
Good.

41:05.422 --> 41:06.923
[Walt] You think these
had something to do

41:07.132 --> 41:08.497
with Gareth's recovery?

41:10.010 --> 41:11.250
What?

41:11.470 --> 41:13.301
[Wait] I found them
in the chapel.

41:13.513 --> 41:16.971
I'm guessing these are
the same anti-depressants

41:17.184 --> 41:19.596
that were recently stolen
from a local warehouse.

41:22.356 --> 41:24.142
Our husbands need those pills.

41:24.358 --> 41:27.771
Our families need those pills.

41:27.986 --> 41:29.567
Don't you wonder
how you got them?

41:29.780 --> 41:30.860
Why should we?

41:31.782 --> 41:34.569
Do you think civilians wonder
where they get their freedom?

41:34.785 --> 41:38.903
No, they just assume it's always
gonna be there -- for free.

41:39.122 --> 41:41.204
[Rebecca] Whoever stole
those pills is a saint.

41:41.416 --> 41:43.407
I'd like to thank them.

41:43.627 --> 41:45.413
You should say
your thank-yous now.

41:45.629 --> 41:47.836
There's a good chance that
person is here in this room.

41:48.048 --> 41:50.630
Look, I don't see any criminals
in here, Sheriff.

41:50.842 --> 41:52.798
Just some good people in need.

41:53.011 --> 41:54.717
[Vic] So, this looks like
it's all of them.

41:56.098 --> 41:57.963
We'll take them back
to the station.

41:58.183 --> 42:00.765
You, me, and Dr. Monaghan.

42:02.312 --> 42:04.177
Is this really necessary?

42:11.279 --> 42:14.817
Dr. Monaghan,
you've already made it clear

42:15.033 --> 42:17.274
that you're passionate
about your work

42:17.494 --> 42:20.782
and that you also feel
frustrated and helpless.

42:20.998 --> 42:22.989
Providing you with clear
motivation to get the pills

42:23.208 --> 42:24.744
to the men and women
you feel need them.

42:24.960 --> 42:26.245
Now we find you
at the very church

42:26.461 --> 42:27.962
where these pills
are being given away,

42:28.171 --> 42:29.786
not to mention
that the gunshot victim

42:30.007 --> 42:31.998
at the warehouse
where the pills were stolen

42:32.217 --> 42:34.208
received very capable first aid.

42:34.428 --> 42:36.419
As if trained by
a medical professional, right?

42:36.638 --> 42:38.503
Yes, I got the implication.

42:38.724 --> 42:40.555
Look, I understand your
suspicions, okay?

42:40.767 --> 42:42.428
But I am not involved in this.

42:42.644 --> 42:45.101
Although, in all honesty,
you know what? I wish I was.

42:45.313 --> 42:47.144
Because it's been such
a roaring success so far?

42:47.357 --> 42:49.268
No, because if I was involved,

42:49.484 --> 42:50.815
I could make sure
that these people

42:51.028 --> 42:53.235
are actually getting
the right medication.

42:53.447 --> 42:56.359
You know, it takes
hours of testing

42:56.575 --> 42:57.781
to make
a proper diagnosis, okay?

42:57.993 --> 42:58.982
You don't just -- just,
you know,

42:59.202 --> 43:00.191
do a couple Google searches,

43:00.412 --> 43:02.027
kick back some anti-depressants,

43:02.247 --> 43:03.236
and hope for the best.

43:03.457 --> 43:04.367
You actually have to know

43:04.583 --> 43:05.538
the person's medical history,

43:05.751 --> 43:07.287
their family history,

43:07.502 --> 43:08.833
-what kind of medication --
-So, you don't support

43:09.046 --> 43:11.037
this kind
of psychiatric vigilantism?

43:11.256 --> 43:12.917
No, I don't.
I understand it,

43:13.133 --> 43:14.464
and I sympathize with it.

43:14.676 --> 43:15.711
But, no, I don't support it.

43:15.927 --> 43:16.882
I think it's dangerous

43:17.095 --> 43:18.676
and short-sighted and reckless.

43:18.889 --> 43:21.505
As reckless as breaking in
to Greg Collette's home?

43:22.267 --> 43:24.303
You know, I have a colleague
who specializes

43:24.519 --> 43:25.804
in aggressive
behavior disorders,

43:26.021 --> 43:27.010
and I can give you his number.

43:28.023 --> 43:30.389
Doctor, you know
where Greg lives.

43:32.611 --> 43:34.272
Come on, Sheriff,
you seem like a smart man.

43:34.488 --> 43:36.649
I mean, really, do I strike you
as the sort of person

43:36.865 --> 43:38.776
who is gonna
throw her medical license away

43:38.992 --> 43:40.948
and bust into a patient's house
guns blazing?

43:41.161 --> 43:42.492
-I mean...
-Well, I've seen things

43:42.704 --> 43:45.036
on this job surprise me more.

43:45.248 --> 43:46.863
You put someone
in a bad enough corner,

43:47.084 --> 43:49.166
they'll do just about anything
to get out of it.

43:49.377 --> 43:50.457
[knock on door]

43:51.880 --> 43:53.165
You're gonna want to hear this.

43:53.381 --> 43:55.087
Excuse me.
I'll be right back.

44:00.055 --> 44:01.511
So, guess who showed up

44:01.723 --> 44:03.259
at Lee McKinnon's house
after he was released.

44:03.475 --> 44:05.090
Sergeant Marc Van Zandt.

44:05.310 --> 44:07.642
He was driving a blue pickup
truck with Colorado plates.

44:07.854 --> 44:10.596
That Zachary identified.

44:11.817 --> 44:13.227
McKinnon let the sergeant in

44:13.443 --> 44:15.024
before he even had
a chance to knock.

44:15.237 --> 44:16.898
He was inside
for just under five minutes,

44:17.114 --> 44:18.775
and then Van Zandt left.

44:18.990 --> 44:22.903
So, obviously, Lee McKinnon
isn't just a victim in this.

44:23.120 --> 44:24.280
It's starting to look like

44:24.496 --> 44:25.827
Lee McKinnon
and Sergeant Van Zandt

44:25.997 --> 44:27.498
were in on this heist together.

44:48.228 --> 44:49.843
Is everything okay?

44:50.063 --> 44:54.602
Why would Lee McKinnon
and Sergeant Van Zandt

44:54.818 --> 44:56.524
break into Greg Collette's house

44:56.736 --> 44:58.692
and steal
Brandi's engagement ring

44:58.905 --> 45:00.520
if Greg's a friend?

45:03.243 --> 45:05.279
-[sighs]
-[footsteps approach]

45:06.496 --> 45:10.956
Seems that the only thing that's
clear right now is the why.

45:11.168 --> 45:13.784
Whoever did this did it to help.

45:14.004 --> 45:15.835
Which brings up another why.

45:16.047 --> 45:17.833
Why do we got to break our backs
to solve this thing

45:18.049 --> 45:19.255
when all the person
was trying to do

45:19.467 --> 45:21.549
is get medicine to people
who needed it?

45:21.761 --> 45:23.012
It's not like anyone was killed.

45:25.098 --> 45:27.760
-Not this time.
-What do you mean?

45:27.976 --> 45:29.841
We've confiscated
all their pills.

45:31.438 --> 45:34.054
What's gonna happen when they
hit again?

45:34.274 --> 45:35.889
Because they will.

46:02.093 --> 46:03.424
What's going on?

46:05.013 --> 46:06.344
My damn engine crapped out.

46:06.556 --> 46:08.217
Well, what do you want me
to do about it?

46:08.433 --> 46:09.934
Well, you can start by doing
exactly what I say

46:10.143 --> 46:11.644
when I say it.

46:11.853 --> 46:13.354
Or you can take your chances
with that grenade.

46:13.563 --> 46:15.349
Shit, man!
Is that thing for real?

46:15.565 --> 46:17.101
You tell me.

46:17.317 --> 46:19.273
-Hands on the wheel!
-Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

46:19.486 --> 46:20.976
Yes, sir. Yes, sir.

46:28.036 --> 46:29.992
Keep your eyes forward!
Don't look at my face!

46:30.205 --> 46:31.411
You're gonna drive us
about a quarter mile

46:31.623 --> 46:32.783
down this road, you understand?

46:32.999 --> 46:34.910
-Yeah, yeah, okay.
-Let's go!

46:47.847 --> 46:49.132
We need to hurry this up.

46:50.183 --> 46:52.174
Take a few more cases,
and that's it, all right?

46:52.894 --> 46:54.475
[Walt]
Stop right there.

46:54.688 --> 46:56.224
Keep your hands
where I can see them.

46:58.400 --> 47:00.140
Get them up.

47:00.360 --> 47:02.225
Off the truck.

47:04.155 --> 47:05.486
Back up.

47:06.408 --> 47:08.273
Move to the van.

47:08.493 --> 47:09.778
Move it!

47:12.122 --> 47:13.237
Tu rn away.

47:14.291 --> 47:16.247
Keep them up.

47:16.918 --> 47:18.078
Keep them up.

47:28.138 --> 47:30.629
Wrist in that hook.

47:30.849 --> 47:32.510
One each.

47:34.060 --> 47:35.095
On the hook.

47:36.146 --> 47:37.352
Do it!

47:38.732 --> 47:40.643
I figured you guys
would still want these pills.

47:41.359 --> 47:42.940
You wouldn't hit
the warehouse again,

47:43.153 --> 47:44.893
so I've been riding
every Zoloft shipment

47:45.113 --> 47:46.444
the last couple of days.

47:46.656 --> 47:47.862
You need to know, Sheriff,

47:48.074 --> 47:49.575
we never meant for anyone
to get hurt.

47:49.784 --> 47:53.242
Is that right?
Tell that to Greg Collette.

48:01.296 --> 48:02.536
Greg?

48:04.257 --> 48:06.873
I thought you were Lee McKinnon.

48:07.093 --> 48:08.958
I'm sorry, Sheriff. I --

48:09.179 --> 48:11.090
Lee McKinnon didn't have
anything to do with this.

48:12.432 --> 48:14.639
Why'd you go to McKinnon's house
after he got released?

48:14.851 --> 48:17.558
We went to his house to make
sure we had our stories straight

48:17.771 --> 48:19.307
and to thank him
for not turning us in.

48:19.522 --> 48:21.353
Lee was supposed to be on break
at that hour.

48:21.566 --> 48:23.272
When he came up on us,
I panicked,

48:23.485 --> 48:26.352
then I fired,
then he fired back.

48:27.655 --> 48:29.782
That's why you got shot
with Lee McKinnon's gun.

48:29.991 --> 48:31.231
Yes, sir.

48:31.451 --> 48:33.112
[Marc]
After Greg left the warehouse,

48:33.328 --> 48:35.944
I cleaned up all his blood,
I took care of McKinnon's leg.

48:36.164 --> 48:37.950
Gave me an opportunity
to talk to him,

48:38.166 --> 48:40.031
explain why we
were after those pills.

48:40.251 --> 48:41.627
He agreed not to talk.

48:48.176 --> 48:50.087
So, the home invasion

48:50.303 --> 48:53.170
was just a cover-up
for your gunshot wound.

48:53.890 --> 48:56.506
No drugged-up robber.
No fight for a gun.

48:57.894 --> 48:59.634
No stolen engagement ring.

49:00.313 --> 49:01.849
I just thought
that if I could make sure

49:02.065 --> 49:04.556
that the other soldiers got
what Brandi didn't,

49:04.776 --> 49:08.189
if they got the help
that she didn't,

49:08.405 --> 49:10.817
I'd have something to live for.

49:18.998 --> 49:20.738
Right.

49:20.959 --> 49:22.915
So, it was just you two
at the warehouse robbery, right?

49:23.670 --> 49:25.285
Yes, sir. That's right.
It was just us.

49:25.505 --> 49:26.790
Except it wasn't.

49:27.006 --> 49:29.258
Greg just got shot.

49:29.467 --> 49:32.379
I don't think you drove yourself
home from the warehouse

49:32.595 --> 49:34.756
and staged that break-in
by yourself.

49:34.973 --> 49:36.133
Marc didn't drive you.

49:36.307 --> 49:37.888
He was busy sewing up Lee.

49:38.101 --> 49:40.057
-So who helped you?
-I did.

49:40.270 --> 49:42.727
Put your gun down
and let these men go.

49:42.939 --> 49:45.430
I don't want to shoot you,
but I will.

49:46.776 --> 49:50.234
I can set down my gun down.
I can't let these men go.

49:50.447 --> 49:52.563
Look, just take his gun
andleave.

49:52.782 --> 49:54.318
We agreed nobody else gets hurt.

49:54.534 --> 49:57.651
I'm not leaving you behind.
Put your gun down.

49:57.871 --> 49:59.111
Put it down!

50:05.420 --> 50:07.160
And the other one.

50:07.380 --> 50:09.336
Put it down.

50:16.222 --> 50:17.723
Then move over there.

50:18.516 --> 50:19.505
Move!

50:20.518 --> 50:21.724
He hasn't seen your face.

50:21.936 --> 50:24.097
He can't identify you,
so just leave!

50:24.314 --> 50:25.520
Leave now!

50:25.732 --> 50:27.142
Rebecca, what are you doing?

50:27.358 --> 50:29.770
I'm not going anywhere
without those pills.

50:29.986 --> 50:32.102
Gareth won't even talk about
seeing someone at the V.A.,

50:32.322 --> 50:35.689
and I'm terrified he's gonna
end up just like Brandi.

50:35.909 --> 50:37.649
Eli needs a father.

50:37.869 --> 50:39.109
Eli needs his mother, too.

50:39.329 --> 50:43.038
If you shoot me,
my deputies will find you,

50:43.249 --> 50:45.661
arrest you, and put you away
for the rest of your life.

50:45.877 --> 50:47.583
Now, you haven't crossed
that line yet.

50:47.795 --> 50:49.296
You can still have a life
with your husband.

50:49.506 --> 50:51.747
Not without those pills,
I can't!

50:51.966 --> 50:53.672
Turn around
and get on your knees.

50:56.804 --> 50:59.056
Get on your knees.

51:00.183 --> 51:01.468
Now.

51:03.228 --> 51:05.560
Get on your knees.

51:19.369 --> 51:21.109
When I lost my wife...

51:23.915 --> 51:26.497
...I just about gave up
on everything.

51:29.462 --> 51:32.420
You can see how losing Brandi
has affected Greg.

51:33.258 --> 51:36.000
Do you think Gareth will be able
to make it without you?

51:36.219 --> 51:38.130
Shut up!

51:49.649 --> 51:51.765
Did you ever read
"Of Mice and Men"?

51:54.487 --> 51:56.352
There's a scene
at the end of the book.

51:58.408 --> 52:01.821
A man named George shoots
and kills his best friend.

52:02.036 --> 52:03.537
It's beautiful.

52:05.498 --> 52:09.867
George kills Lennie
to save him from being lynched.

52:11.337 --> 52:14.829
When I read the book,
I didn't realize

52:15.049 --> 52:17.791
how any act can become
an act of love.

52:18.011 --> 52:20.002
-[gun cocks]
-Rebecca, no!

52:24.934 --> 52:29.394
You think if Gareth could see
your act of love right now...

52:29.606 --> 52:31.847
he might go get the treatment
he needs?

52:34.736 --> 52:36.852
Maybe he doesn't even need
to see it.

52:37.739 --> 52:39.570
He just needs to hear about it.

52:44.704 --> 52:46.865
If you set your gun down,
Rebecca,

52:47.081 --> 52:50.539
we could call Gareth right now.

52:55.006 --> 52:57.588
It'd mean more if he heard it
from you, I think.

53:09.646 --> 53:10.931
[gun clicks]

53:17.111 --> 53:18.942
[sobbing]

54:02.740 --> 54:04.196
[Walt]
Sorry to keep you waiting.

54:04.409 --> 54:05.398
[clears throat]

54:06.160 --> 54:07.661
It's been a long week.

54:09.706 --> 54:11.367
It's been a long year.

54:12.250 --> 54:15.617
Anyway, um, clearly,

54:15.837 --> 54:18.544
you're the two best candidates
for this job.

54:20.800 --> 54:22.210
I'm not sure either one of you

54:22.427 --> 54:24.292
has demonstrated
what I need to see.

54:27.265 --> 54:28.971
ReaHy?

54:29.183 --> 54:31.435
So, you're not gonna offer
the job to either of us?

54:31.602 --> 54:33.934
[Walt]
No, I'm not.

54:34.147 --> 54:36.012
Maybe I've rushed into
this process too quickly.

54:36.232 --> 54:41.147
Maybe -- Maybe I'm holding you
to unrealistic standards.

54:41.362 --> 54:44.104
Yeah, well, maybe you don't know
what the hell you're doing.

54:45.616 --> 54:47.402
I don't know if you
realize this.

54:47.618 --> 54:50.075
I was doing you a favor
by even applying to this job,

54:50.288 --> 54:52.700
going through
this whole ridiculous process.

54:52.915 --> 54:55.497
It's no wonder your last deputy
ran against you as sheriff.

54:55.710 --> 54:57.826
If I wasn't so afraid
I'd end up dead like him,

54:58.045 --> 55:00.081
I'd do the same damn thing!

55:01.674 --> 55:03.210
It's a joke.

55:05.052 --> 55:06.462
[door slams]

