56:11.118 --> 56:12.449
The next thing I remember,

56:12.662 --> 56:14.698
l was waking up
in a hospital room.

56:17.208 --> 56:18.948
The nurse told me I'd been shot
three times

56:19.168 --> 56:20.874
and that Phil was dead.

56:23.714 --> 56:25.454
I'm sorry.

56:27.051 --> 56:28.632
That must have been hard.

56:28.845 --> 56:33.714
Yeah, I went through
every stage.

56:35.059 --> 56:39.598
Anger, guilt, denial,
back to anger again.

56:40.481 --> 56:43.063
But then, uh, I ran into

56:43.276 --> 56:44.891
one of my brother's
work buddies,

56:45.069 --> 56:49.312
and he introduced me to tai chi.

56:50.783 --> 56:52.774
And it saved me.

56:52.994 --> 56:54.734
How so?

56:56.455 --> 56:58.286
I like to put it like this.

56:59.500 --> 57:02.162
I went to church a lot as a kid.

57:02.378 --> 57:05.620
And we were always taught
to love our enemies.

57:06.632 --> 57:09.749
Tai chi taught me
something new --

57:09.969 --> 57:13.461
to love the enemy inside me,
as well.

57:15.349 --> 57:17.385
So I don't look at peace

57:17.602 --> 57:19.684
as the absence of conflict
anymore.

57:20.605 --> 57:23.893
I see it as the acceptance
of conflict.

57:30.489 --> 57:32.901
I finally finished your book.

57:33.117 --> 57:34.323
Um...

57:35.995 --> 57:37.656
Glad I did.

57:44.795 --> 57:47.002
[Walt]
So, what would you have done

57:47.214 --> 57:49.876
